df <- MASS::Boston
set.seed(1290)
train_idx <- sample(1:nrow(df), size = nrow(df) * 3/4, replace = F)
train <- df[train_idx, ]
test <- df %>% anti_join(train)

x_train <- train %>% dplyr::select(-medv)
y_train <- train$medv
x_test <- test %>% dplyr::select(-medv)

ymat_train <- as.matrix(y_train)

make_ice_data <- function(model, var, x, n = 100) {
    var_ind <- which(colnames(x) == var)
    col <- x[, var]
    range <- c(min(as.numeric(col)), max(as.numeric(col)))
    diff <- range[2] - range[1]
    delta <- diff/n
    vars <- seq(range[1], range[2], length.out = n)
    x_pred_list <- lapply(vars, function(v) {
        new_data <- x
        new_data[, var_ind] <- v
        pred <- predict(model, newdata = new_data)
        cbind(new_data[, var_ind], pred) %>% data.frame() %>% setNames(nm = c(var, 
            "pred")) %>% rowid_to_column()
    }) %>% setNames(str_c("sim", str_pad(1:n, width = 5, side = "left", pad = "0")))
    x_pred_list
} %>% bind_rows

make_pdp_data <- function(ice_data, var) {
    ice_data %>% group_by(!!sym(var)) %>% summarize(pred = mean(pred)) %>% add_column(rowid = max(ice_data[[1]]) + 
        1, .before = 1)
}

plot_ice <- function(ice_data, ice = T, pdp = T, ice_alpha = 0.3, pdp_color = "darkorange", 
    pdp_size = 1.2) {
    var_name <- names(ice_data)[2]
    pdp_data <- make_pdp_data(ice_data = ice_data, var_name)
    
    if (c(pdp, ice) %>% all) {
        ggplot() + geom_line(data = ice_data, aes(x = !!sym(var_name), y = pred, 
            group = rowid), alpha = ice_alpha) + geom_line(data = pdp_data, 
            aes(x = !!sym(var_name), y = pred), color = pdp_color, size = pdp_size) + 
            theme_bw() + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(size = 12), axis.text.y = element_text(size = 12), 
            axis.title.x = element_text(size = 14), axis.title.y = element_text(size = 14))
    } else if (c(!pdp, !ice) %>% all) {
        ggplot()
    } else if (pdp == F) {
        ggplot() + geom_line(data = ice_data, aes(x = !!sym(var_name), y = pred, 
            group = rowid), alpha = ice_alpha) + theme_bw() + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(size = 12), 
            axis.text.y = element_text(size = 12), axis.title.x = element_text(size = 14), 
            axis.title.y = element_text(size = 14))
    } else if (ice == F) {
        ggplot() + geom_line(data = pdp_data, aes(x = !!sym(var_name), y = pred), 
            color = pdp_color, size = pdp_size) + theme_bw() + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(size = 12), 
            axis.text.y = element_text(size = 12), axis.title.x = element_text(size = 14), 
            axis.title.y = element_text(size = 14))
    }
}

ice_nox <- make_ice_data(model = xgb_01, var = "nox", x = xmat_train, n = 100)

colnames(xmat_train) %>% lapply(function(vname) {
    ice <- make_ice_data(model = xgb_01, var = vname, x = xmat_train, n = 20)
    plot_ice(ice, ice = F, pdp = T, pdp_color = "dodgerblue", pdp_size = 1.2)
})

gam_01 <- model <- gam(medv ~ s(crim) + s(zn) + s(indus) + chas + s(nox) + s(rm) + 
    s(age) + s(dis) + rad + s(tax) + s(ptratio) + s(black) + s(lstat), data = train, 
    family = Gamma(log))
plot(model, residuals = T, se = F, pages = 2)

pred <- predict(model, newdata = test, type = "response")
plot(test$medv, pred, main = "GAM")
curve(identity, add = T)

cat(" RMSE =", rms_err(test$medv, pred))
 RMSE = 4.051147
